shows.title: "BLESSED"
shows.overview: Supreme presents, "BLESSED" a full length video directed by William Strobeck featuring Tyshawn Jones, Ben Kadow, Sean Pablo, Aidan Mackey, Na-kel Smith, Sage Elsesser, Vincent Touzery, Kevin Bradley, Rowan Zorilla, Kevin Rodrigues, Mark Gonzales, Jason Dill. . .

shows.title: #GeorgeWashington
shows.overview: Meet the Father of Our Country in a whole new way as historians analyze George Washington's voluminous correspondence. Setting out his contacts and letters in the modern framework of a Facebook profile gives Washington's busy and productive career a new transparency.

shows.title: #NoJoke
shows.overview: A viral campaign to bring awareness to school bullying brings musician and philanthropist Andrew Cole face-to-face with his childhood tormenter.

shows.title: #O2LForever
shows.overview: Join Connor Franta, Jc Caylen, Kian Lawley, Ricky Dillon, Sam Pottorff and Trevor Moran as the YouTube supergroup Our 2nd Life (O2L) embarks upon their 2014 North American tour. Step inside their journey, from blogging in their bedrooms to performing in front of screaming fans across the country. This 95-minute adventure captures their launch into the next level of stardom while they try to stay grounded and maintain authentic connections with the communities that started it all.

shows.title: #UNFIT: The Psychology of Donald Trump
shows.overview: Medical doctors and mental health professionals go on camera, on the record, for a discussion and science-based examination of the behaviour, psyche, condition, and stability of former President Donald Trump.

shows.title: #artoffline
shows.overview: What happens to art in the Internet age' The philosophers, artists and exhibition makers in this documentary believe that endless reproduction liberates art from a muddled art market and an undemocratic exhibition circuit. A couple of critics wonder whether the urge for physical objects is really just a nostalgic fetishism. But aren't we losing something if the physical artworks disappear?

shows.title: $100 and a T-Shirt: A Documentary About Zines in the Northwest
shows.overview: In just under an hour, "$lOO & a T-Shirt" brings zine culture to life! Using broken and borrowed equipment, Joe Biel illuminates the world of self-publishing. He gives us glimpses of the Portland Zine Symposium, takes us on a a zine-themed bicycle tour around Portland, and interviews local zinesters.
shows.originalTitle: $100 and a T-Shirt: A Documentary About Zines in the Northwest

shows.title: $uperthief: Inside America's Biggest Bank Score
shows.overview: A firsthand look at the life of career-criminal, Mafia associate and one of the most successful bank robbers in U.S. history, Phil Christopher.

shows.title: '85: The Greatest Team in Football History
shows.overview: A look at the 1985 Chicago Bears and their road to the Super Bowl. Featuring interviews with players, former coach Mike Ditka, and famous Bears fans.
shows.originalTitle: '85: The Greatest Team in Football History

shows.title: 'Tis the Season: The Holidays on Screen
shows.overview: A celebration of beloved holiday films and TV specials; featuring decades of rich archival footage and interviews with the celebrities, directors and pop culture experts unwrapping the most memorable and festive moments on screen.
shows.originalTitle: 'Tis the Season: The Holidays on Screen

shows.title: 'Twas the Fight Before Christmas
shows.overview: In this true-life twist on a holiday fable, Jeremy Morris brings a whole new meaning to Christmas spirit when his extravagant seasonal display sparks a dispute with his neighbors that lands them all in court.

shows.title: (A)sexual
shows.overview: Inside a sex-obsessed culture, people who dont experience sexual attraction struggle to claim their identity amid a mountain of public misconception.

shows.title: (Dis)Honesty: The Truth About Lies
shows.overview: Behavioural scientist Dan Ariely discovers the complicated truth behind what happens when we lie to each other.

shows.title: (In)Visible Portraits
shows.overview: Oge Egbuonu celebrates the heritage and history of Black women in America.

shows.title: 0.56% What happened to Mexico?
shows.overview: In 2006, Felipe Caldern won the presidency of Mexico with an advantage of 0.56%. This documentary explains the polarization of Mexican society, how a society transformed the struggle for power and ended up confronted like never before.

shows.title: 007 - For Our Eyes Only
shows.overview: Este fascinante documental es una mirada detrs de escena de los actores, escenarios y dispositivos de la legendaria franquicia de espas.

shows.title: 1 Billion Orgasms
shows.overview: A middle-aged engineer decides to prove his worth by inventing a device he dreams will make him responsible for one billion orgasms.

shows.title: 1 Mountain
shows.overview: Hunter Wood is one of the best skiers in the world.  Struggling for direction in his life he decides to test his limits on the most treacherous mountains in North America.
